title: For Sale:  *Rare* SKS Accepts AK Magazines *Pre-Ban*
postcontent: This is not the average sks that you come across everyday in your local gun shop. This is an actual sks from the factory to accept the AK magazine. Made by Norinco and only imported from 1988-1989. This is the Pre-Ban sks that accepted ak magazines. Pre-Ban meaning the 922r ban. Later years, the sks-m was imported. You tend to see a lot more of those. They have the thumbhole stock and no bayonet. This type of rifle is referred to as the SKS-D which was simply a made up term to classify these types of rifles by the importer. SO there wont be any such marking on the receiver. However this is a numbers matching rifle, complete with bayonet, cleaning rod, and trap door cleaning kit. Total of 3 steel magazines. All original and has not been altered. The only thing not original is the two screws on the sides of the stock that hold the magazine well in place. This is truly a collectors item and not something to be turned into a tapco turd.
